***********Jenkins Common Errors***********
1. Java Heap Out-Of-Memory Error (Jenkins JVM)
#Out of memory can occur on both Master and Worker nodes. It depends on where the JVM or job is running.
UI dies → Master OOM
Build fails → Worker OOM

Solution: 
Increase JVM heap memory size by modifying JENKINS_JAVA_OPTIONS environment variable (Ex: -Xmx2g for 2GB)
Go to -> vi /etc/default/jenkins

Ex: JAVA_ARGS="-Djava.awt.headless=true -Xms512m -Xmx4096m"

sudo systemctl restart jenkins
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Build stuck in queue.
# Insufficient executors
# Locked Resources
# Hanging Build 

Solution: 
1. Check the executors available, node status, 
2. Increase the no of executors on Jenkins.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Permission Denied Error
# No permissions to access a file/directory

Solution: 
Check the jenkins users has a enough permissions and adjust security settings if required.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Jenkins slave agent disconnect
# Due to network issues, firewall settings, JVM crashes on agent.

Solution: 
Check network connectivity, firewalls open, review logs for JVM crash reports or memory.

